  "bio_raw": "Naima Khatun is currently serving as a Senior Lecturer in Accounting at University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh (ULAB)⁠. She has previously worked as a lecturer at Bangladesh University of Business and Technology (BUBT)⁠, American International University-Bangladesh (AIUB)⁠, Northern University Bangladesh (NUB)⁠, and University of Information Technology and Sciences (UITS)⁠. She completed her BBA and MBA in Accounting from University of Dhaka and later obtained a Research Master’s degree in Business Administration from Kobe University, Japan.\nShe also gained one year of teaching and research experience at Kobe University Business School, where she worked alongside internationally renowned professors and researchers from different parts of the world.\nHer teaching areas mainly include Financial Accounting, Managerial Accounting, and Intermediate Accounting. She is passionate about student-centered learning and integrating practical knowledge into accounting education.\nNaima Khatun has published seven research articles, including six international publications, and has participated in several national and international conferences. Her research interests primarily focus on Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR), Carbon Disclosure, and Corporate Governance. She is particularly interested in sustainability reporting, modern slavery, and the role of governance in enhancing corporate accountability and long-term organizational performance.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Sustainability Accounting, Corporate Governance, Carbon Disclosure."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nMaster of Arts in Business Administration\n, KOBE University, Japan.\nMBA\n, University of Dhaka.\nBBA\n, University of Dhaka."
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Conferences\nPresented Paper titled as “Corporate Response to Carbon Emissions: Focusing on Scope 3” in ‘The 2nd International Conference on Business and Economics’ organized by University of Dhaka on October 30-31, 2017.\nInternational Conference titled as ‘The 6th Asian Management Research and Case Conference 2017’ jointly organized by Six Universities, Dhaka, Bangladesh.  Date: May 23, 2017.\n“The 7th International Conference of the Japanese Accounting Review” organized by Kobe University, Japan. Date: January 07, 2017.",
    "Journal Articles\nKhatun, N.\n, Rahman, M. M. (2017). Corporate Response to Carbon Emissions: Focusing on Scope 3. Journal of Business Studies (Special International Edition), 2(1), 1-28.\nRahman, M. M., &\nKhatun, N.\n(2017). A Comparative Analysis of Corporate Governance Guidelines: Bangladesh Perspective. Asian Journal of Business Environment, 7 (2), 5-16.\nRahman, M. M., &\nKhatun, N.\n(2017). Quality of Corporate Governance: A Review from the Literature. The Journal of Asian Finance, Economics and Business, 4(1), 59-66.\nKhatun, N.\n, Yagi, M., & Kokubu, K. (2016). Carbon Disclosure in response to institutional pressure in Japan and Southeast Asia. Discussion paper series, Graduate School of Business Administration, Kobe University, Japan.\nRahman, M. M., &\nKhatun, N.\n(2016). Intellectual Capital: A Review from the Literature. International Journal of Industrial Distribution and Business, 7(4), 5-10.\nKhatun, N.\n, Naima, J., Karim, Z., & Alam, L. (2016). Importance of Annual Report to the Shareholders: Empirical Evidence from Bangladesh. The Journal of Asian Finance, Economics and Business, 3(3), 67-77."
  ],
